<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0486 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a short time, imaging using digital subtraction angiography (DSA) hasbecome widely accepted for both diagnostic and therapeutic vascular procedures.The authors' assessment that DSA would offer significant advantages overconventional film radiology for interventional radiographic procedureshas been confirmed in their initial experience with this imaging modality.In this chapter the authors review current application of DSA to embolotherapyand angioplasty procedures and potential future contributions of digitalimaging to evaluating and understanding vascular disorders and treatment.</TEXT></DOC>